LR_remarks22: This original Lincoln Log Home will make a wonderful home or commercial location. This home has a spacious interior, gorgeous woodwork and mountain views. It has a fantastic and nicely landscaped yard complete with a brook, trail access for snowmobiles and ATV's. All you will need to do is move in. Large open living room and kitchen and dining area. Full master bedroom and bath on the first floor. Bedroom and half bath up on the second level and large family room in the walk out basement along with a 3/4 bath, and another bedroom as well as an office space or potential fourth bedroom. Large attached two car garage with storage above joins the house with a welcoming entryway.

LR_remarks22: Surrounded by open fields, a private pond, gardens and peaceful vistas, Fleetwood Hill Farm exudes warmth and grace. Sited on 101.84+/- pastoral acres, historic charm and unique features encompass the 8,100 square-foot, five bedroom residence. This 1790's Colonial has been tastefully renovated and expanded to include finely appointed entertainment spaces, game room, gym and master suite. Two patio areas and a screened porch offer outdoor dining opportunities. The master suite encompasses a private dressing room with a fireplace, en suite bath with fireplace, Jacuzzi tub and large, tiled shower. The recently renovated 1797 barn offers 11 stalls, tack room and grain rooms, abundant hay storage and an attached two-car garage. Guest Cottage and Caretaker's Log Cabin offers accommodations for guests and employees. Moultonborough Airpark is 14 miles distance. Portland, ME is 63 miles, Manchester, NH is 68 miles, and Boston, MA is 112 miles from Tamworth, New Hampshire.

LR_remarks22: Coot Farm is one of those extraordinary properties that rarely come on the market. Sited on 600 acres, this remarkable home features nearly 15,000 sq. ft. of living space with 3 levels that are completely accessible via an elevator. Quality exudes throughout the home. The family or great room can accommodate family and friends along with the game room with pool table. The chef's kitchen is well equipped and offers plenty of space with a dining area with a wall of windows overlooking one of four ponds and pastures below. The butler's pantry and spacious dining room make this a perfect home for entertaining. The living room with stone fireplace and features the stunning spiral staircase to the 2nd floor. The amazing master bedroom suite offers a grand view of the property all the way to Nippo Mountain. The huge master bath features radiant heat. There are 2 more bedrooms, 2 baths and a magnificent trophy room. You will be drawn to the lower level where you can read to your heart's content in the beautiful library. It is a gem. There is another bedroom on the lower level with full bath and then there is the Olympic 4 lane indoor swimming pool surrounded by radiant heat. Relax in the sauna and steam room or enjoy a workout in the exercise room complete with locker room. From the 3 car garage there is access to the chapel and the breathtaking observatory with observation deck that opens to the sky above. A truly breathtaking property that must be seen to truly appreciate.
LR_remarks2020: US 202/9 to Barrington, to Canaan Back Rd. Property is on the right.

LR_remarks22: While it might look like this property has been on the market for a long time, It was not until recently that it was finally  fully approved by the Campton Planning Board  to be able to be sold.  During that time the owners had the lot(along with the other two beside it ) selectively cut for a potential homesite and gave it  roughed in area for the driveway.  THERE ARE NO RESTRICTIONS COVENANTS so you can do anything you want with in Campton's  zoning regs for residential/commercial zone which the property falls in,  this 3 room rough camp appears structurally sound on post and Piers with 5.62 acres includes over 300 feet frontage on Town Pound Road. It has  great plateaus for you to move the cottage back off the road  & give it a foundation .Now that the lot has had selective cutting you can  definitely see  the local mountain views .The property was not clear cut so there are still many trees on the property & now you can see that while there are some steep parts ,the are great parts with rolling  old farm land , beautiful granite rocks to help you with your landscaping & more. Taxes are to be determined as it is currently being taxed as part  of 17 acre Perfect property to finish off camp into guest house and use it until you can build a home or use the camp as your vacation basecamp . Site your house in so you have all the privacy of not see  neighbors and yet only a mile or so to the interstate . 5.62 acres not enough there are 2-  5+ acre lot on the left also for sale

LR_remarks22: Historic 1798 Colonial. This 2468 square foot home features 4 Bedrooms, many Original Features including Hand Planed Doors and Woodwork, 5 Working Fireplaces, Wide Pine Floors, Beamed Ceilings, an attached Barn, and loads of charm. Situated on 1 Acre, this property also INCLUDES the TUFTONBORO GENERAL STORE, U.S. Post Office, & 2 - 1 Bedroom APARTMENTS above, totaling an additional 2808 Sq. Ft.. The Tuftonboro General Store dates back to 1822 and is one of the few remaining Original New Hampshire General Stores still in daily operation. It is the heart of the community and could provide a wonderful income opportunity. For anyone with a love of history and looking for a new beginning this home and its attached businesses are a 'Must See' property. See NNEREN MLS #4684545 for COMMERCIAL version of this listing. $50,000 PRICE REDUCTION . Property is being sold "AS IS". The Sellers are retiring after 19 years as StoreKeepers.

LR_remarks22: A simpler life, a thoughtful place, a breathing space..Sited with views to majestic Mount Monadnock and continuing to the edge of Bowker Pond in Fitzwilliam NH is this special 2 bedroom log cabin at the edge of the woods on 6.5+/- Acres.  For some 40 years it has been the place to go to be still, to read, to discuss the issues of the day, to focus differently.  Many hours have been spent on the enclosed porch, enjoying the breezes of summer and the sounds of the woods and fields.  Many nights have been warmed by the glow of the fireplace and the crackle of the kindling and logs ablaze.  Two bedrooms, full bath, a good working space kitchen, stone fireplace, separate woodstove, electric baseboard.  The basics, so that you can focus on the essentials of life. An adjacent lot of 8 +/- Acres is available for sale for $225,000.

This iconic structure has long been a local landmark. House and tenant apartment building behind it  have been unoccupied for 10+ years and need complete rehabilitation to be habitable. Sold "as is." Sellers have little information on the house structure, systems. Buyers should exercise their own due diligence. Home could again be a significant one with expansive views of Mascoma Lake and beyond.  There is the possibility of purchasing more land. 156 acres of the original farm land, is on the market for $550,000 (MLS 4737631). The entire 252+ acre property could be purchased and is listed for $1,450,000 (MLS 4776652)

LR_remarks22: Make your dream of owning your own Inn come true! 6 guest rooms with private baths, restaurant and tavern/bar. Located a few steps away from beautiful Bow Lake. Seller has done all the work and has renovated and restored this beautiful Inn. With gunstock timber frame, numerous timeless details have been maintained to help remind us of a simpler life. The Bow Lake Inn is ready for the new owner to take it the next step to full operation. Local area and towns are longing for an eatery and gathering place which also provides overnight accommodations for visiting family, weddings or tourists. Selling fully furnished and equipped. Henry Miller antique grand piano completes the dining room next to the fireplace. Major systems updated:400 amp electrical, plumbing, state approved septic, roofs, heating systems and central A/C. Dining room and tavern. Full service license to serve food for 22 seats (licensed for food, bakery, catering, retail food sales and functions). 1st floor has 2 guest rooms, one w/kitchenette. 2nd floor has 4 additional guest rooms and 1 workers quarters. 3rd floor suite for inn keeper/owner. Commercial grade kitchen--too much equipment to list. 29 parking spots. Handicap access - no steps on entire first floor w/2 handicap restrooms. Walk out basement w/additional baking area, locked storage for liquor, walk in cooler and 3 washers and 2 dryers. Conveniently located between Concord and Portsmouth. Possible owner financing. See virtual tour.

The timeless style, modern luxury, and charming history of this magnificent estate are highlighted in the main home with over 7,000 sq ft of living space. The property's unique, thoughtful design boasts a warm, inviting living room with enormous stone fireplace and stunning Belknap Mountain views. It's all about the details in the marvelous master suite with a fantastic shower in the silo structure. Hidden rooms and red slate counter tops add to the charm. This home is the ideal space for entertaining with a butler's kitchen and enormous dining room in the beautifully updated original homestead. Perfect for family gatherings or large dinner parties, there's plenty of room for guests to spend the night. Situated in the mountains just minutes from Lake Winnipesaukee, this is the perfect vacation or year-round home. Luxury, recreation, and relaxation await!

LR_remarks22: Imagine listening to birds chirping while swaying in a hammock on your New Hampshire Island oasis on the shores of Lake Winnipesaukee! Just 2 hours north of Boston, Big Barndoor Island awaits. As seen in the film, On Golden Pond, this sought-after island is situated between Wolfeboro & Alton.  The property consists of a 4-bedroom home & a 3 story bunkhouse. Located in Alton on 2.17 acres, this Adirondack style property is on a double lot & has 200 feet of Lake Winnipesaukee frontage which can be best viewed on the sunny oversized deck. An oversized U-Shaped Dock accommodates up to four boats, a stone staircase leads a swimming area. 1st floor living has 2 bedrooms, a washer & dryer, & full bath. Main living area has tall ceilings & offers splendid lake views. The fireplace offers plenty of warmth. A screened porch is off the living room. A spiral staircase leads upstairs to a 1/2 bath, additional living space & two additional bedrooms with skylights & lake views. A catwalk leads to a detached bunkhouse. The 1st floor of the bunkhouse contains a bedroom, the 2nd floor has three bunkbeds that sleep nine, and 3rd floor has a family room with captivating views of the lake. Wolfeboro, The Oldest Summer Resort in America, is easily accessible via 5-minute boat ride & offers the convenience of shopping, dining, summer concerts and more. Sold fully furnished. The 2nd lot can be sold, or kept for additional privacy. Call today to arrange a guided tour!
LR_remarks2020: Northwest Side of Big Barndoor Island, facing toward Wolfeboro Town Docks.  Number 216 is on U shaped dock.

Quintessential New England farm or commercial venture; you decide.  This property has it all.

LR_remarks22: Working from home? Need to escape from urban and city life? This beautifully crafted 5 bedroom, 5  bath 9,000 square foot home is situated very privately on 70 glorious acres of fields and forest in one of America's best small towns  Lebanon, New Hampshire.  There are clearly defined office areas so you can stay home. If you need to travel from the compound there is an airport, shopping and hospital within minutes. Completed in 1991, the main structure of this unique and charming home includes a magnificent great room, professionally equipped kitchen, spacious media room and bar area, office and library spaces with built-in bookcases, work-out room, indoor lap pool, elegant porches and so much more. Photos can't adequately capture the fit and finish and feel of the interiors; they must be experienced to fully appreciate the quality and craftsmanship. The delightful stand-alone structure at the entrance to the property was built to be book barn but could be adapted for any number of uses. The attached 3 car garage includes a large storage area above. With excellent schools, top-notch medical facilities and a regional airport, this property is well situated and suitable as a family residence or executive retreat. Dartmouth College and Vermont are minutes away. Possibilities abound here. Information packets are available along with private tours.
LR_remarks2020: From RT 89 take exit 19 and head west, at the first stop light turn left onto Poverty Ln. The house is on the right. No drive by's please!!

LR_remarks22: Class A office building with private penthouse apartment with all of the luxuries and amenities youd expect to find!  Beautifully landscaped and located in the heart of the New Hampshire Seacoast and minutes to I-95 and the Mass and Maine borders.   Penthouse apartment has gourmet/chefs kitchen with five-burner Wolf gas stove with custom tiled backsplash, double ovens and Thermador fridge.  Gas heated fireplace, all stainless with granite counters, beautiful custom made cabinets and granite farmers sink. Large walk-in pantry and private porch area off kitchen for BBQ and growing all your herbs! Master bathroom has a (wheelchair accessible) dual expansive walk-in shower with travertine lime stone tiles, a deep soaking tub and radiant heated floors. Gorgeous alder hardwood throughout  distressed hardwood floors, architectural beams in kitchen, solid hardwood doors.  Elevator opens to a private grand entrance foyer with beveled glass French doors and with a private entrance to a spacious guest suite with a private bathroom and tiled shower. Many architectural custom features throughout in including tray ceilings, large stone gas fireplace in living room, beautiful crown moldings, and high-end tiles.  Property is handicapped accessible and the open kitchen, dining and living areas are perfect for entertaining!  Office building consists of 12 class-A office suites with shared waiting areas and large conference room.  Most suites are separately metered. Property has 42 parking

LR_remarks22: Perfectly maintained and beautifully restored Federal Colonial Circa 1830. Built by Leonard Farley a renowned covered bridge builder in his day. Many original features are intact including 7 fireplaces, wide pine floors, timeless moldings and raised paneling. Extending behind the original home is a 60' long ell which encompasses the open updated kitchen complete with granite counter tops and stainless steel appliances. Extending from the kitchen is the great room once the carriage house. Unique continuous transom windows extend the entire east side of the ell. This room provides for wonderful family and entertainment space with original hewn beams spanning the 10.5' high ceiling. ARCHITECTURALLY REDESIGNED BARN FEATURES 2,500+SQ.FT. MAKES IT PERFECTLY SUITED FOR AN IN HOME OFFICE WITH ENDLESS INCOME GENERATING OPPORTUNITIES. LEAVE THE BIG CITY OFFICE ENVIRONMENT AND LIVE, WORK AND ENJOY YOUR OWN SAFE HAVEN.  Consider converting into a separate living space.  Could be converted into a multi generational family compound. A private courtyard separates the main home and a 1840sq.ft. two story cape style structure.  Complete with its own septic and C/A. Unique opportunity to own 3 picturesque sprawling acres zoned for business/residential use. The location has great visibility in the heart of this quintessential community. Steps from the town center with shops and attractions. Price listed under assessed valuation.
LR_remarks2020: Broad Street to Ash.  Ash street is just past Brookdale farm on the right.  Front of home is on Broad Street.  Entrance to property is on Ash.  Private property. Must have an appointment to enter property.

LR_remarks22: 5007C-This nice home located on Hall Road in Errol NH is situated on 67 acres of land. The home features 3 bedrooms two 3/4 bathrooms, one full bathroom, and 4 fireplaces (one with a gas insert). The master bedroom with fireplace and bathroom are located on the first floor. The cozy living room features one of the fireplaces and also has a nice picture window to let in the light and to enjoy the views. During those cold winter nights enjoy dinner in the dinning room with its fireplace with gas insert keeping you warm. The dinning room also has a nice picture window and access to the front porch through the sliding doors. Off from the dinning room is located a nice office space or another bedroom with a fireplace and sliding door leading out to the spacious back yard. The home has a spacious kitchen with a breakfast bar and a sky light to fill the room with natural lighting. Just off from the kitchen is the laundry room and a 3/4 bathroom. LR_remarks22: This is an exceptional opportunity to buy 2 recently renovated homes on 2 separate lots totaling 1.93 +/- acres on Rt. 115 in the village of Twin Mountain, NH.  Each home has 200-amp electrical service, town water with private septic. Live in one home and rent the other while running your business or rent both homes and the garage! Currently operating as a successful auto repair, towing and auto sales business permitted and licensed with the State and Town, just minutes to Bretton Woods and not far from Cannon Mtn, snowmobile trails as well as ATV trails and I- 93. This property has many possibilities. There are currently only 2 businesses on Rt.115.  The main home has spacious interior just shy of 1700 feet, easy to heat- multiple heating options include a 185K btu FHW heat, a very efficient 45,000 btu Harmon pellet stove and an 85K BTU gas heater. Stainless steel appliances, gas stove and a stand-by 18K generator. The second rental home has newer appliances, a remodeled bathroom as well as both bedrooms.  Both are updated and ready to go! ALL stock inventory and permits & licenses for the business are included with the sale.

LR_remarks22: Truly a hidden gem in a place where you wouldn't expect to find it.  Maine, Vermont, Western Mass?  Upstate New York or Northern New Hampshire?  Sure, but to find 33+ acres that's perfectly suitable for horses or farming in the heart of Bedford, NH?  Yes!  Come see all the creature comforts this gated property offers.  From the masculine look of a brick exterior on this nearly 7000 SF Contemporary Colonial complete with an in-ground pool,  tennis court, pond, and barn suitable to transform into your horse barn.  The interior is as warm and welcoming as the exterior is bold.  The Kitchen is the hub of this home with authentic La Heartland Professional appliances.  Enjoy your 2+ story exposed gable Family Room with a floor to ceiling stone fireplace.  Also off the Kitchen is the Living Room and game room as well as the Dining Room.  The Library/Office offers privacy and functionality to it's users.   Rich cherry floor to ceiling built-ins is sure to put wind in your sails.  Simply magnificent!  The 2nd floor with 5 bedrooms each with their own ensuite baths.  The finished space over the garage is perfect for an au pair suite.  This is a must-see for anyone who covets the acreage and open privacy this estate offers with all the natural conveniences of being 15 minutes from Manchester-Boston Regional Airport, an hour to Boston, the seacoast, the lakes and mountains.  It's also a perfect property to take off the grid with it's own pond and plenty of real estate for solar trackers.

Historic 1848 schoolhouse just minutes from Alton Bay.  Seasonal views of Mount Major.   With no immediate neighbors you can get away from it all while still not being far from anything either.  Great hiking, swimming, restaurants and attractions nearby. Hand-hewn beams in main bedroom/schoolhouse, fruit trees and 2 sheds.  Level lot on the side of a mountain! Home needs updating and repair but the location and lot are highly desirable.
LR_remarks2020: Route 11 to Alton Mountain Road.  House is on the left after Avery Hill Road and Alton Town Forest

LR_remarks22: 5043c OUT THERE! For those of you looking for that remote camp this is it. At the end of Ridge Road is this post and beam cabin that will delight hunters, fisherman, hikers, and family's that just want to be out there. The view takes you into the valley and distant mountains. This camp has a concrete footer and concrete block foundation. The larger portion of the building is post and beam construction being one big room where everyone gathers and enjoys the warmth from the wood/coal stove. Kitchen is off the Great room and leads into a dining area and the comfort of another wood stove. Sleeping quarters on second floor one room five beds and then to a loft with ability to have more beds. A brook runs through where a dug well is in place. Water line from well underground to inside camp is not hooked up, but very easy to do. Septic system installed 500 gallon plastic tank with conventional leach field of stone and pipe. Camp is wired for generator. Electric is nearby. Snowmobile access.

LR_remarks22: Hill House is located In Sandwich, NH. Here you will find the unique combination of a private mountain retreat with sweeping views across Gorgeous Squam Lake to the distant mountains and phenomenal Sunsets across the lake and a sandy beach on Squam Lake. You will quickly learn why the this Lake has adopted the name of "On Golden Pond ". This property is unique as it is rare for any property with with 365 feet of water frontage to offer this much privacy. Located high on a hill with 41+ acres  with hiking access to Eagle Cliff and Red Hill trails directly out you back door. The beach area offers outstanding views across the lake as well as docking and a swim raft. The home faces the lake with a wall of windows for allowing for great light in the home and always looking at the outstanding views. The home has beautiful stone fire place, large family room, 4 bedrooms, sleeping loft, an office currently being used as a guest room, nice deck and beautiful large screen porch for you to enjoy on summer evenings. Radiant floor heat by oil and a back up generator and you are set to enjoy property year round. Property has conservation easement on property and ROFR held by Squam Lakes Conservation Society to ensure property remains protected for generations to come. Also property is in "current use" which means lower property taxes! Subject to weekly summer rentals. SAS pending.

LR_remarks22: Set in the heart of New Hampshire's beautiful Monadnock region, on a picturesque country road, Overlook Farm exemplifies the true definition of a gentleman's farm. The main house, a brick colonial built in 1850 consists of 6 bedrooms, 7 baths, wide pine floors, bar room, multiple fireplaces, handcrafted finishes thorough out and is surrounded by 76 pristine acres of pasture and forest. Additionally, there are multiple outbuildings, a 2 bedroom 2 bathroom guest cottage, an equipment barn with managers office and 1 bedroom caretakers apartment, and several garage bays for storage of equipment and supplies. The "Entertainment barn", complete with a full kitchen and loads of character, creates the the perfect setting for anything from a business meeting to an exclusive dinner party. No detail was overlooked, glass walls allow you to admire the Herefords grazing, while the exposed hand hewn beams and antiques bring you back to a simpler time. The landscape is accented by beautiful gardens, classic New England stone walls and several ponds. The greenhouse, tennis court and fitness studio provide the ability to pass the time in peace and tranquility. LR_remarks22: The historic Runnymede Farm is an extraordinary part of Seacoast history. Originally owned by MA Governor Alvin Fuller, Runnymede Farm is located on the south side of Atlantic Avenue in North Hampton on the banks of Little River, an estuary that provides access to the Atlantic Ocean. The Farm originally included over 200 acres of land where, Peter Fuller, a well-known businessman, philanthropist and thoroughbred expert bred and kept horses there until the early 1980s. During this time Fuller owned the famous, albeit contentious, 1968 Kentucky Derby Winner Dancers Image.   This offering constitutes the substantial working equestrian Farm at Runnymede. The Farm is comprised of a 4080 sf barn, 3000 sf caretaker residence, expansive paddocks, a riding/jumping arena and other high-end equestrian amenities. The barn boasts 12 stalls, a central hay drop, bathing bay with hot and cold water, heated tack room, office, kitchen and two 1/2 baths. There is an outdoor kitchen and fire pit to enjoy during the Seacoast s warmer 3 seasons. An additional 1150 sf barn provides additional equestrian possibilities and storage. In addition, significant infrastructure has been upgraded to provide for a potential indoor riding ring or for a potential estate lot. There are endless opportunities for an equestrian facility and a sizable riverfront estate lot at this iconic property.
LR_remarks2020: Traveling east toward the Ocean on Atlantic Avenue, the Property will be on your right just before the historic Runnymede Farm billboard.
